# Javascript, React, Typescript

- Any javascript import with `~/` works from the `app/javascript` directory, so any javascript/typescript file can safely import from there. Examples:
 -`~/components` which will resolve to `app/javascript/components`
 -`~/lib`, `app/javascript/lib`, respectively.

- We have a list of graphql queries: [queries.ts](mdc:app/javascript/lib/queries.ts)

## Using scripts

[package.json](mdc:package.json)

- Always run `npm run lint` from our package.json in order to find any linting problems.

- Always run `npm run format:check` from our package.json to see if prettier styles should be applied. You can run `npm run format:check -- --write` to automatically apply prettier styles where possible


